<strong><li class="about">Importing Contacts</li></strong>

<ol start="A" type="A">
	<strong><li>Importing Contacts Within the “Edit Profile” Settings</li></strong>
		<ol start="1" type="1">
			<li>Once signed in to your account, click on the “Profile” link in the upper right hand corner of the website.</li><br>
			
			<li>Click on the <img src="<%= root_url %>images/About/Import Contacts.jpg"> button in the “EMAIL SETTINGS” section in the lower right hand corner of the page.  
				Our site uses the Plaxo plug in to import your contacts; you should see the following pop up once you click on the Import Contacts button:<br>
<img src="<%= root_url %>images/About/Plaxo.jpg"></li>
			
			<li>Click on the radio button next to the Email Provider that you use then click "Next".</li><br>
			
			<li>Enter in your username and password and click "Sign In".</li><br>
			
			<li>Plaxo will now bring up a list of all of your contacts.  You can either scroll through this list and put a check mark next to the contacts that you want to import, or you can just select the "Check All" option above the "Back" button and all of your contacts will be selected.  Once you've selected all of the contacts you want to import, click the "Next" button.  If you forget to import certain contacts or want to add additional contacts some time in the future, just go through these steps again.</li><br>
			
			<li>Plaxo should now display a message that says "Your contacts have been added".  Click the "Done" button.  Campusmack will now save all of your contacts in our protected database for easy retrieval; this might take a while so just wait until the website re-routes you to a page with all of your contacts listed.</li><br>
			</ol>
			
		<strong><li>Importing Contacts Through the "Send as Smack" Function</li></strong>
		<ol start="1" type="1">	
			<li>Once signed in to your account, click on the <img src="<%= root_url %>images/About/Send as Smack.jpg"> button on any Campusmack post.</li><br>
			
